                <h1>How Life Reached the Galapagos Islands</h1>
                <p>Organisms arrived at the Galapagos Islands through processes such as drifting on ocean currents, flying, or being carried by wind. Over millions of years, these species adapted to the isolated environment, leading to unique evolution. This isolation allowed diverse life forms to thrive, making the islands a living laboratory of evolution.</p>
